.TH "kvm_phys_addr_ioremap" 9 "kvm_phys_addr_ioremap" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_phys_addr_ioremap \- map a device range to guest IPA
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kvm_phys_addr_ioremap
.BI "(struct kvm *kvm "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t guest_ipa "  ","
.BI "phys_addr_t pa "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "bool writable "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "kvm" 12
The KVM pointer
.IP "guest_ipa" 12
The IPA at which to insert the mapping
.IP "pa" 12
The physical address of the device
.IP "size" 12
The size of the mapping
.IP "writable" 12
Whether or not to create a writable mapping
